---
import BaseLayout from '@layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Breadcrumb from '@components/ui/Breadcrumb.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About eBikeLocal — Why We Built This Directory"
  description="Learn how eBikeLocal aggregates dealer and brand data, how our editorial process works, and how we verify shop listings."
>
  <div class="mx-auto max-w-4xl px-(--spacing-page) py-8">
    <Breadcrumb items={[{ label: 'Home', href: '/' }, { label: 'About' }]} />

    <h1 class="mt-6 text-3xl font-extrabold text-surface-900 md:text-4xl">About eBikeLocal</h1>

    <div class="mt-6 space-y-6 text-surface-700 leading-relaxed">
      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-surface-900">Why this exists</h2>
        <p class="mt-2">
          eBikeLocal started from a simple problem: brand dealer locators are fragmented, inconsistent, and hard to compare.
          Riders were forced to open one brand site after another just to figure out which nearby shops actually carried the bikes they wanted to test.
        </p>
        <p class="mt-2">
          We built eBikeLocal to make that process faster and more transparent: one place to discover local shops, compare brands, and shortlist bikes.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-surface-900">What makes our data different</h2>
        <p class="mt-2">
          Our core dataset aggregates dealer information across 15+ brand locator sources, then enriches and validates those records with geography and Google Places data.
          That brand-level aggregation is what allows city and shop pages to show which brands are likely available in one view.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-surface-900">Editorial and data standards</h2>
        <p class="mt-2">
          Buying-guide recommendations are based on spec review, category fit, safety-relevant components, and price-to-value analysis.
          For shop data, we run normalization and deduplication checks, then flag edge cases for manual review.
          Claimed listings and direct merchant updates can override generated descriptions to improve listing quality over time.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-surface-900">Disclosure</h2>
        <p class="mt-2">
          Some outbound product links may be affiliate links.
          Read our full policy on the <a href="/disclosure/" class="font-medium text-brand-600 hover:underline">Affiliate Disclosure</a> page.
        </p>
      </section>
    </div>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
